      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TIGER ROARS (6) drew on the back row at his most recent outing so did well to work home for second, beaten 1.3 metres, in a far better performance at Globe Derby. Finds the right race so can return to the winners' circle. MY ULTIMATE BANJO (5) led and faded at his latest appearance but was going well prior, recording three straight placings at Globe Derby. He has the ability to mix it with them. Manners have let ICE QUEEN (7) down in her last two outings but she came from this row to win at Globe Derby three back. No harm in drawing here with the sprint lane to rely upon. If she behaves a big run is likely. I NEED AGIRLFRIEND (1) resumes after a year but has trialled and gets the ace draw so keep safe.",
